728250f-b.title: Queens: Wyckoff Avenue - Halsey Street
728250f-b.text:
Wyckoff Ave., south side, east from Halsey Street (trolley tracks
swing into it). At the S.E. corner of Halsey Street and Wyckoff Ave. is
the Elks Park Hotel (Election sign displayed thereon) erected by Christian
Homeyer about 1898. This building seen in a set of two views was de-
molished in 1930.
1922.
View 2: March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726320f-a.title: Queens: Centre Street - Wyckoff Avenue
726320f-a.text:
Centre Street, north of Wyckoff Ave., showing in the far background
the 5-story Public School No. 77. The garage at the right is No. 1638.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

728247f-a.title: Queens: Wyckoff Avenue - Center Street
728247f-a.text:
Wyckoff Ave., east from Center Street. The Avenue in 1849 was
known as Ridge Road.
December 1924.
